                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "   Details of method of analysis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "U.Fasoli",
                "D.Toniolo",
                "G.Zago",
                "V.Benzi",
                "P.L.Ottaviani",
                "L.Zuffi"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Elastic and inelastic scattering of neutrons by Na",
                " at 8.0,9.7 and 14.1 MeV-"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "2ITYPAD"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "   The 5.5 MeV van-de-graaff accelerator",
                " of the University of Padua was used for the 8.0 and",
                " 9.7 MeV experiments."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "ACCEL"
                ],
                "institute": "2ITYPAD"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 400 keV pulsed ion accelerator of",
                " the Padua University was engaged in the 14.1 MeV",
                " measurement"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "   D-d reaction was used for the 8.0 MeV",
                " neutrons by means of a deuterium gastarget at 1 atm",
                " (4.5cm thick)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "A-BE"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  The 9be(alpha,N)12C reaction was used to",
                " produce the 9.7 MeV neutrons.The targets were",
                " metallic be (0.3 mg/cm2), evaporated on tungsten and",
                " gold backings."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "   For the 14.1 MeV neutrons the d-t reaction in",
                " a tritium target, bombarded by 10ns long deuteron",
                " beambursts, bunched to 1.5ns, was chosen."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The 23Na scatterer (49.93g,99.5pc purity) is melted",
                " in an aluminium can (height 6.9cm X 3.12cm outer",
                " diameter)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   For details see U.Fasoli et Al.,Nucl.Phys.",
                " A125(1969),227.",
                ".For the 14.1 MeV experiment see U.Fasoli et Al.,",
                " Inin/be-70/10(1970).",
                ".The flightpaths were-",
                " 2.9m for the 8.0 MeV,",
                " 2.0m for the 9.7 MeV,",
                " 4.0m for the 14.1 MeV neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STANK"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron detector consists of a Ne213",
                " liquid scintillator (4in. In diameter X 2in. Thick)",
                " on a xp1040 photomultiplier.",
                ".The efficiency was determined by means of the N-P",
                " scattering method.As scatterer served a polythylene",
                " zylinder (1.5cm outer diameter,12.6g)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "           .The cross section values were obtained",
                " from the normalized counts in the corresponding",
                " peaks of the time-of-flight spectra and by",
                " comparison with the known N-P differential cross",
                " section."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Optical and statistical model fits,using coupled-",
                " channel and hauser/feshbach calculations,were",
                " carried out for the presented experimental data and",
                " data of other authors at lower energies(F.G.Perey",
                " and W.E.Kinney,report ornl-4518(1970),P.Kuijper et",
                " Al.,Nucl.Phys.,A181(1972,545)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "STATUS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Differential elastic and inelastic cross section",
                " data taken from cec-(73) 7."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Both elastic and inelastic data were corrected for",
                " attenuation.",
                ".The elastic and first excited level data were also",
                " corrected for multiple scattering.",
                ".The corrections were carried out by means of the",
                " MONTE CARLO method and also according to S.A.Cox,",
                " nucl.Instr. And meth.56(1967),245.",
                ".The inelastic data values represent an upper limit",
                " because of the presence of a low energy tail in the",
                " source neutron energy distribution."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Errors include statistical uncertainties and",
                " uncertainties in the efficiency of the neutron",
                " detector (+-10 % max.)."
              ]
            }
          ],
